219. Contains Duplicate II
Solved
Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return true if there are two distinct indices i and j in the array such that nums[i] == nums[j] and abs(i - j) <= k.

Example 1:

Input: nums = [1,2,3,1], k = 3
Output: true
Example 2:

Input: nums = [1,0,1,1], k = 1
Output: true
Example 3:

Input: nums = [1,2,3,1,2,3], k = 2
Output: false
 

Constraints:

1 <= nums.length <= 105
-109 <= nums[i] <= 109
0 <= k <= 105

Approach:
i use comparison to ith index element to i+1th,i+2th ...... elements , but not exceeds k (because this problem simply want difference between indices of same element lesser or equal to k)

Solution:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsNearbyDuplicate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int size = nums.size();
        if(size == 1 && k == 0)
            return true;
        if(size == 1 && k > 0){
            return false;
        }

        for(int i=0;i<size; i++){
            
            for(int j = i+1; j <= i+k && j<size; j++){
                
                if(nums[i] == nums[j]){
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};
